The paper deals with sampling a large unknown graph to estimate a given metric of interest. This involves designing a random walk on a weighted graph that preferentially crawls nodes and edges that convey greater information regarding the target metric. The paper also employs the theory of stratification to find optimal node weights for a given estimation problem. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
